HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1206
By Terry
A RESOLUTION to honor Rick Insell on the occasion of his
retirement as the women's basketball coach at
Middle Tennessee State University.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in paying tribute
to a legendary coach, skilled tactician, and inspirational motivator who has experienced great
success during his forty-nine years in high school and college basketball; and
WHEREAS, Rick Insell, head coach of the Middle Tennessee State University (MTSU)
women's basketball team for the past twenty-one years, has announced that he will take his
much-deserved retirement at the conclusion of the 2025-2026 season, thus ending the most
successful era in the history of the program; and
WHEREAS, Coach Insell is the winningest basketball coach in MTSU history with 505
wins, having won at least 20 games in eighteen of his twenty-one seasons and at least 25 wins
in nine seasons; and
WHEREAS, Coach Insell has led his alma mater to twenty conference championships,
(ten regular season titles and ten conference tournament titles) and thirteen conference
championship games; and
WHEREAS, his Lady Raiders teams have made twenty-one consecutive postseason
appearances, including twelve NCAA Tournament bids and seven WNIT bids; and
WHEREAS, sixty-six players on teams led by Coach lnsell have earned All-Conference
honors, seven have been named All-Americans, and five have been selected in the Women's
National Basketball Association draft; and
WHEREAS, he is the only basketball coach in NCAA history to produce three
consecutive NCAA scoring champions and the only coach in history to win more than 500
games at both the NCAA Division I level and in high school; and
