- 1 -

WHEREAS, a legend in his profession, Coach lnsell has received five Conference
Coach of the Year awards in recognition of his prowess, and he is a nine-time Hall of Fame
inductee, including the Women’s Basketball Hall of Fame, Tennessee Sports Hall of Fame, and
Conference USA Hall of Fame; and
WHEREAS, Coach Insell has posted 1,279 wins in his peerless career, a total that
includes 775 wins over twenty-eight seasons as the girls' basketball coach at Shelbyville Central
High School; and
WHEREAS, he won ten TSSAA Class AAA state championships and two USA Today
national titles at Shelbyville Central and earned four national coach of the year honors; and
WHEREAS, Coach Insell's high school coaching accomplishments also include a
national-record 110-game winning streak during which the Golden Eaglettes won four
consecutive state titles (1989-1992); and
WHEREAS, Coach Insell's passion for the game, his commitment to graduating his
student athletes, and his leadership in creating a championship culture have defined MTSU
women's basketball for more than two decades; and
WHEREAS, he has positively influenced many lives during his tenure at MTSU, and he
will forever be part of the school's athletic community; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor Rick Insell, the winningest coach in Middle Tennessee State
University basketball history, on the occasion of his retirement as the school's women's
basketball coach, salute his forty-nine years of excellence in the sport, and extend to him our
best wishes for much continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
